positions.description:
Work at Tweag I/O includes:

* Architecting cloud-based Excel version that supports different language kernels including R and Python. The solution worked with intermediate size data, few Gb datasets and supported novel technology for translation Excel formulas into SQL expression.

* Implementation network-transport-zeromq abstraction layer that can be used for Cloud Haskell;

* Participated in building HaskellR - interop solution between R and Haskell (see link below);

* Is one of the Cloud Haskell (distributed-haskell) Platform contributors;

* Participated in writing StaticPointers extension for GHC compiler;

* Writing verification models for simple distributed algorithms;

* Implementation of the FRP like event processing engine (not announced yet).
